p: The DPPH-HPTLC (1,1-diphenyl-2-picrylhydrazil—high performance thin layer chromatography) bioautographic assay ( Figure 3) indicated that β-caryophyllene (36.23%), trans-γ-bisabolene (10.04%), cis-γ-bisabolene (8.33%), and trans-β-farnesene (7.81%) were the major compounds responsible for the lower scavenging activity at R f 0.9 ( Table 1).
